The paper proposes a deep learning model for clinical endpoint prediction using electronic health records. This involves dealing with multiple heterogeneous temporal events such as lab tests, diagnosis, and drug administrations. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), clinical informatics (cs.CE), and databases (cs.DB).
